.TH "create_var_ref" 9 "create_var_ref" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
create_var_ref \- Create a variable reference and attach it to trigger
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct hist_field *" create_var_ref
.BI "(struct hist_trigger_data *hist_data "  ","
.BI "struct hist_field *var_field "  ","
.BI "char *system "  ","
.BI "char *event_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hist_data" 12
The trigger that will be referencing the variable
.IP "var_field" 12
The VAR field to create a reference to
.IP "system" 12
The optional system string
.IP "event_name" 12
The optional event_name string
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Given a variable hist_field, create a VAR_REF hist_field that
represents a reference to it.

This function also adds the reference to the trigger that
now references the variable.
.SH "RETURN"
The VAR_REF field if successful, NULL if not
